11 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
12 Sec. 1. FINDINGS AND PURPOSE
13 (a) It was the stated intention of the framers of the Constitution of the
14 United States of America that Congress should be “dependent on the people
15 alone” (James Madison or Alexander Hamilton, Federalist 52). That
16 dependency has evolved from a dependency on the people alone to a
17 dependency on those who spend excessively in elections through campaigns or
18 third-party groups—the result of the U.S. Supreme Court ruling in Citizens
19 United v. Federal Election Commission, 130 S.Ct. 876 (2010). Citizens United
20 removed restrictions on independent political spending, resulting in a legally
