5 Sec. 3. 17 V.S.A. § 2941 is amended to read:
6 § 2941. LIMITATIONS OF CONTRIBUTIONS
7 (a) In any election cycle:
8 (1)(A) A candidate for State Representative or for local office shall not
9 accept contributions totaling more than:
10 (i) $1,000.00 from a single source; or
11 (ii) $1,000.00 from a political committee.
12 (B) Such a candidate may accept unlimited contributions from a
13 political party.
14 (2)(A) A candidate for State Senator or for county office shall not accept
15 contributions totaling more than:
16 (i) $1,500.00 from a single source; or
17 (ii) $1,500.00 from a political committee.
18 (B) Such a candidate may accept unlimited contributions from a
19 political party.
